title: For Sale:  CZ75 Pre-B 9MM
postcontent:
For sale is a CZ75 9mm "Pre-B" in 9mm.  This is an Israeli police trade in pistol and although it has fairly significant holster wear as seen in the pictures the internals are in very good condition and it shoots great.

This is what is considered a "Pre-B" due to the old style safety with detent hole, rounded hammer and trigger guard and was manufactured before firing pin blocks were required on pistols and therefore does not have one.  The lack of a firing pin block makes for a very smooth and light single action trigger pull, arguably one of the best you can find in a CZ75.

I have replaced both the hammer spring and recoil spring for good measure with replacements from Cajun Gun Works.

Comes with one magazine.  9MM ammo available as well if interested.

title: For Sale:  Century RAS 47 AK47 7.62x39 - Latest Model
postcontent:
I purchased this rifle about 3 months ago and miss my AR. 
100% US Made this is a very nicely built rifle. Clean crisp trigger with a nice break, and it is a double hook. Typically single hooks have better pulls because there is less surface area but this is a trigger than needs no work. Impressive, with the added bonus of double hook. Should one hook break (unlikely), you still have a backup and trigger group still functions flawlessly.

I fired about 100 rounds through it. 
Comes with a 30rnd Magpul PMag which fits tightly into the magwell; no wobble.
This rifle is known to be very accurate; 1 M.O.A. which is exceptional for the AK platform. Especially in a stock rifle. 
Black nitride finish is very tough. Dust cover is solid, no rattle. Wider T-bar mag release. 
Black nitrided barrel rivals chrome lined barrels in longevity.
Side rail scope mount. 
Accepts standard AK furniture if you wanted to change it out. 
I Adjusted the safety so it is nice and smooth. Easy to slide on and off with positive detent positions. It won't move unintentionally.
Stamped receiver with perfectly seated rivets; not crushed in and not standing too high.
Its a nice shooter but I just find myself more comfortable with the AR platform with 5.56. 


Note: picture shows aftermarket muzzle break and grip which are not included. I already sold those to a buddy with an AK. It will come with the standard slant break and century grip.
